\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Gene editing technologies, such as CRISPR-Cas9, have revolutionized the field of biotechnology by allowing precise modification of an organism's DNA. This groundbreaking tool holds immense potential for addressing genetic diseases, developing new treatments, and improving crop yields. Key components of gene editing include guide RNA, Cas9 enzyme, and donor DNA template. Ethical considerations and regulatory frameworks are essential for responsible application of this technology.}